          %p.ocall
            Code Across America is a distributed event when the national Code for America network contributes to the "Code for America Effect" at (roughly) the same time.
          %p.ocall
            Code Across America is an event that any municipality can join, big or small, beginner or expert. Individuals and groups can Code Across America, whether you join the social media conversation [LINK], commit to a GitHub [LINK], or participate in one of the many events to be held around the country [LINK].
          %p.ocall
            Events will be hosted in Fellowship and Brigade cities across the U.S. between 22-24 February. February 23rd is also 
            %a{:title => "International Open Data Day", :href => "http://opendataday.org"} International Open Data Day.
            Join Code Across America and International Open Data Day by joining or hosting an event where you live. 
          %p.ocall
